snippet.textDisplay:
This is why I moved to Montana - you've just seen some of the biggest crimes and police activity here.

The headlines of a fire in Stevensville was front page and they had lots of pictures... the most fire activity in many years.

Love it!

With just above a million residents in the third or forth largest state in the lower 48 - crime does not pay - and nobody gets away.

Just be careful of the black bears - they can charge at 35 MPH and they will let you watch as they eat your liver.
